Package: faLearn
Title: Machine Learning using Whole Genome Sequence Data
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Alessandro", "Gerada", , "alessandro.gerada@liverpool.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6743-4271"))
Description: This package supports the use of whole genome sequence data as an input to machine
    learning models to predict an output phenotype. Functions are provided to generate $k$-mer
    counts in data formats suitable for XGBoost, as well as functions to download and process
    whole genome sequence data stored in the Pathosystems Resource Integration Center (2013)
    <doi:10.1093/nar/gkt1099> database or locally.
